  "post_text": "📌 Writing Code Worth Reviewing\n\n🛑️ Just spent 6 hours fixing last night's automated code generation \"savings\" on production. 💥\n\n**Myth → Reality**\n\n1️⃣ **Myth: Automated code generation reduces\nReality: It often creates more debt, hidden in poorly understood AI-generated code. 💀\n\n2️⃣ **Myth: AI can replace human expertise**\nReality: Human judgment and code review are still essential for quality and maintainability. 🤖\n3️⣿ **Myth: Automated code is always correct**\nReality: AI can make mistakes, especially if the training data is incomplete or inaccurate. ❌\n\n**Prevention Strategies**\n1️⃣ Review AI-generated code carefully\n\n2️⃣ Ensure AI training data is accurate\n\n3️⃣ Implement human code review\n\n4️⃣ Monitor AI performance metrics\n\n5️⃣ Re-evaluate AI-generated code over time\n\n6️⃣ Foster a culture of human expertise\n\n**Poll:** What's your approach to code quality in a world dominated by AI?\n\nA) Automated code generation with no review\nB) Human code review for all critical code\nC) AI-assisted coding with occasional human review\nD) Replacing human engineers with AI tools\nE) Focusing on AI training data quality only\nF) Implementing AI monitoring and optimization metrics\n\n#SystemDesign #SoftwareArchitecture #DistributedSystems #ScaleEngineering",
